cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with learning target appearance in online multi-target tracking. It also involves the use of linear classifiers and minimum residual errors, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses a dataset and features commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper's focus on tracking and optimization suggests it may also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO).
